Program: Outlook
Title: I survived a serial killer's attack
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0112t40
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 4 Dec 2012
Rose Steward, the Californian woman who talked a rapist out of killing her by pretending to be in love with him. With her attacker on Death Row, we hear why she's campaigning against capital punishment. Also, we meet Satoru Arishiro, the Japanese policeman turned unofficial zookeeper. Picture: Rose Steward Image credit: Henry Young Show less